cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.MM

This paper is about using scribbles to annotate images for semantic segmentation, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes an algorithm to train convolutional networks, which falls under the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper uses a graphical model to propagate information, which is related to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions the PASCAL VOC and PASCAL-CONTEXT datasets, which are commonly used in computer vision research and fall under the sub-category of cs.GR (Graphics). Finally, the paper discusses the use of scribbles in commercial software, which could be related to cs.MM (Multimedia).
